00:00:00.909 --> 00:00:04.900
Today, we're going to show you how to make a lemon meringue pie.

00:00:04.900 --> 00:00:07.600
To make a lemon meringue pie, you need to do a sugared pastry.

00:00:07.600 --> 00:00:17.600
To do a sugared pastry, you need : 100 grams of iced sugar, 125 grams of butter, 250 grams of flour, 1 egg, 1 pinch of salt.

00:00:17.600 --> 00:00:29.600
Instructions : Put the butter 10 seconds in the microwave, then put it in a recipient and soft it with a fork.

00:00:29.600 --> 00:00:40.100
Add the iced sugar, the salt to the butter mixture and blend the preparation.

00:00:40.100 --> 00:00:48.500
Add the egg to the butter mixture and blend  with a whisk.

00:00:48.500 --> 00:00:56.500
Add the tamised flour to the preparation.

00:00:56.500 --> 00:01:01.200
Knead it to have a ball with the pastry.

00:01:01.200 --> 00:01:04.200
Put it in the fridge for 45 minutes.

00:01:04.700 --> 00:01:18.700
To continue the recipie we have to do a lemon cream. To make it you need : 50 grams of butter, 2 lemons, 120 grams of sugar, 4 egg yolks (keep the 4 eggwhites)

00:01:18.700 --> 00:01:25.300
Instructions : press the lemons.

00:01:25.300 --> 00:01:48.360
In a recipient blend egg yolks and sugar and add pressed lemons, mix it.

00:01:51.800 --> 00:02:01.830
Heat the egg mixture over a low fire, sturring constantly until thick.

00:02:03.300 --> 00:02:14.300
Remove it and let it cool. Then add the butter to the mixture, mix and let it in the fridge.

00:02:16.400 --> 00:02:20.400
Remove the sugared pastry's preparation from the fridge and knead it a bit again.

00:02:20.500 --> 00:02:30.300
Put some flour on the cutting board, spread the pastry on it with your hands.

00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:49.310
Then cut it in 4 parts and flat them. Repeat this action a couple times, and put the pastry in the fridge again.

00:02:50.500 --> 00:03:00.530
To make the italian meringue, you need : 240g of sugar, 4 eggwhites (the ones you had for the lemon cream) and a little glass of water.

00:03:02.500 --> 00:03:15.540
Instructions : put the sugar in a pan and add water. Heat it over a low fire until mixture's temperature is 118 degrees.

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:31.050
Beside : beat the egg whites until stiff.

00:03:31.050 --> 00:03:43.100
Pour the sugar and water mixture over beaten egg whites, sturring constantly until it's getting cool. Reserve it for later.

00:03:43.500 --> 00:03:47.600
Preheat the oven to 170°C (340°F)

00:03:47.600 --> 00:03:57.600
Take the sugared pastry from the fridge and spread it on the cutting board with a rolling pin.

00:03:57.600 --> 00:04:03.500
Cut your pastry to have a circle adjusted to your dish that you will use.

00:04:04.500 --> 00:04:20.500
Coat your rolling pin with flour. Then, wing the pastry round it.

00:04:20.500 --> 00:04:28.600
Roll out the pastry in your dish.

00:04:29.600 --> 00:04:39.600
Prick pastry with a fork.

00:04:39.600 --> 00:04:50.600
Put the dish in the oven during 20 minutes.

00:04:50.600 --> 00:05:05.600
Remove the dish from the oven.

00:05:05.600 --> 00:05:15.600
Let the pastry getting cool and pour your lemon cream on it.

00:05:29.600 --> 00:05:41.600
Put the italian meringue in a pastry bag fitted with a fluted tip.

00:05:41.600 --> 00:05:48.600
Using the pastry bag fitted with a fluted tip, decorate your pie of the italian meringue.

00:05:58.600 --> 00:06:18.600
Burn with a cook's blowtorch the top of the pie.

